1- Subnets promising all revenue will be used for purchasing alpha
2 - Subnets promising certain emissions will be burnt. 
3 - Subnet 64 @namoray moving to single validator, promising not to game the system 
4 - Subnet 51 @Fish | lium.io moving to single miner, promising to distribute alpha to useful miners

I think there is a strong incentive for subnets not to abuse these promises (else quickly punished) but it's not ideal. Its also not ideal workarounds are needed to avoid wasted compute. 

I agree with @consτ [τ, τ] Uber analogy - exponential growth vs cost to a degree - but without workarounds in 64 and 51 -  its difficult to create a subnet incentive that avoids paying uber drivers for empty rides. Uber wouldn't have grown with this handicap.

1: Somewhere - potentially Root validators - should police subnet owner promises - are they truly buying alpha with all their revenue?
